			linux-headers-rpi-2712
Description: PamirAI Signal Aggregation Module DKMS driver
 This package provides DKMS (Dynamic Kernel Module Support) driver
 for the PamirAI Signal Aggregation Module (SAM). The driver implements
 a highly optimized 4-byte packet protocol for bidirectional communication
 between Linux host systems and an RP2040 microcontroller via UART.
 .
 Supported platforms:
  - Raspberry Pi CM5 (BCM2712)
  - Rockchip RK3566 (Radxa Zero 3W)
 .
